[30;1m65 | [0m[35m* Core library objects should represent (`__repr__`) themselves in accordance[0m

[30;1m67 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m68 | [0m[35m  > If at all possible, \[the string returned by `__repr__`\] should look like[0m
[30;1m69 | [0m[35m  > a valid Python expression that could be used to recreate an object with[0m
[30;1m70 | [0m[35m  > the same value (given an appropriate environment).[0m
[30;1m71 | [0m[35m[0m
